  "text": "Questions regarding food preparation were used as a proxy to measure confidence in specific skills required for simple food preparation. The children were asked how confident they were in four key cooking tasks: cutting fruit and vegetables, measuring ingredients, following recipe instructions and making a pasta salad. Cooking confidence was measured using a scale, where 1='I can't do this at all', 2= 'I need a little help', 3='I need a lot of help', and 4='I can do this on my own' (based on [CITATION_1] . These questions were asked of children in both the intervention and control groups pre and post intervention.",
